<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{title}}</title>
    <style>
        @page {
            size: A4;
            margin: 1in;
        }
        
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 40px;
            font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            color: #333333;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        
        .header {
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #2563eb;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        
        .document-title {
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #1e40af;
            margin: 0;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }
        
        .subtitle {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #6b7280;
            margin: 10px 0 0 0;
            font-style: italic;
        }
        
        .section-header {
            font-size: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #1e40af;
            margin: 30px 0 15px 0;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
            padding-left: 15px;
        }
        
        .subsection-header {
            font-size: 16px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #374151;
            margin: 20px 0 10px 0;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        
        .content-text {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #4b5563;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            text-align: justify;
        }
        
        .bullet-point {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #4b5563;
            margin-left: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            position: relative;
        }
        
        .bullet-point::before {
            content: "•";
            position: absolute;
            left: -15px;
            color: #2563eb;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        
        .highlight-box {
            background-color: #f8fafc;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        
        .highlight-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #1e40af;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 40px;
            padding-top: 20px;
            border-top: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
            color: #6b7280;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
        
        .company-logo {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #1e40af;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1 class="document-title">{{title}}</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Professional Document Generation Made Simple</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section-header">Quick Start Guide</div>
    
    <div class="subsection-header">Step 1: Set Up Your Brand Kit</div>
    <div class="content-text">Your brand kit ensures every document reflects your professional identity:</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Navigate to Settings → Brand Kit</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Add your company name and description</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Upload your logo (PNG, JPG, or SVG format)</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Select your brand colors (primary and secondary)</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Choose your preferred fonts</div>
    
    <div class="highlight-box">
        <div class="highlight-title">Pro Tip:</div>
        <div class="content-text">A complete brand kit automatically applies to all generated documents, maintaining consistent professional appearance across all your business communications.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="subsection-header">Step 2: Choose Your Document Type</div>
    <div class="content-text">MM Docs offers 25+ professional document categories:</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>HR & Employment Documents:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Offer Letters - Professional job offers with terms and conditions</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Employment Contracts - Comprehensive employment agreements</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Experience Certificates - Official work experience validation</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Policy Documents - Company policies and procedures</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>Legal & Compliance:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDAs) - Confidentiality protection</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Service Agreements - Professional service contracts</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Terms of Service - Platform and service terms</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Privacy Policies - Data protection and privacy compliance</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>Sales & Marketing:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Business Proposals - Client project proposals and pitches</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Quotations - Detailed price estimates and service quotes</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Company Profiles - Professional business overviews</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Sales Emails - Persuasive client outreach communications</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>Finance & Accounting:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Invoices - Professional billing documents</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Purchase Orders - Procurement authorization documents</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Receipts - Payment confirmation records</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Financial Reports - Business financial summaries</div>
    
    <div class="subsection-header">Step 3: Fill in Document Details</div>
    <div class="content-text">Our intelligent forms capture exactly what's needed for each document type:</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">HR documents require employee information, positions, and company details</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Legal documents need party information, terms, and effective dates</body>div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Sales documents require client details, project scope, and pricing</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Finance documents need transaction details, amounts, and due dates</div>
    
    <div class="content-text">The more specific information you provide, the more professional and accurate your generated document will be.</div>
    
    <div class="subsection-header">Step 4: Generate and Download</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Review your inputs for accuracy</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Click "Generate" to create your document</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Preview the generated content with your branding applied</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Download in PDF format for sharing or DOCX for editing</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Save to your document library for future reference</div>
    
    <div class="section-header">Best Practices</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>For Optimal Results:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Complete your brand kit before generating documents</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Provide specific, accurate information in forms</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Review generated content before finalizing</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Keep your brand kit updated with current information</div>
    
    <div class="content-text"><strong>Document Quality Tips:</strong></div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Use clear, professional language in input fields</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Include all relevant details for comprehensive documents</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Verify dates, names, and amounts for accuracy</div>
    <div class="bullet-point">Customize content to match your business tone</div>
    
    <div class="highlight-box">
        <div class="highlight-title">Start Creating Today</div>
        <div class="content-text">Ready to transform your document creation process? Select any document category from the dashboard to begin generating professional, branded documents that enhance your business communication and save valuable time.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <div class="company-logo">MM Docs</div>
        <div>Professional Document Generation Platform</div>
        <div>AI-Powered Business Solutions</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>